result.formatted_address: 116 Fuk Wing St, Un Chau, Hong Kong
result.name: Baodao Gu Zao Beef Noodle Restaurant

reviews.text: Many choices and food are reasonable price. Food are above average. Love the noodle which is al dente and tasty. Qantities is above average. Chicken chop is crispy and yummy.

Good restaurant, good quality. their noodles are their specialities so you must try their Taiwanese beef noodles soup signature.. it's delicious and not expensive.. count 50-70HKD per dish. The quantity is good too. their chairs design let you put your bag under them.
Atmosphere is very nice. There is no english menu here. Food is average along with the pricing. Can get salty with some dishes. The drinks here are nice but more on the sugary side also.

The decorations here are very local to Taiwan. Many Taiwanese drinks to choose here at a very reasonable price. A wide variety of local Taiwanese food.

The beef was tender with tasty sauce. I am not a big fan of Taiwanese food but I think these were quite good. Do give it a try!

Best Taiwanese beef noodles in Hong Kong. It's better on some days than others but when it's on a good day it's the best in HK I've had. Price is reasonable for the quality but very expensive for the area. Drinks taste great. I like their noodles more than famous places in Taiwan. Probably top 3 Taiwanese beef noodles for me in the entire world. (My favorite is in LA in the US)

result.adr_address: 香港元洲福榮街116號
result.name: 寶島古早牛肉麵

reviews.text: 蚵仔煎👎
用心做，有係台北第一次食牛肉麵嘅感覺，祗係冇咁重藥材味，而且老闆娘都重視客人嘅意見。
好食，牛肉做得好食，麵就少咗啲（男子唔夠食），女子剛剛好。
食物尚算不錯，但在深水埗區來說價錢偏貴，有很多其它選擇。
